&lt;h4&gt;Added&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/Azure/azure-cosmos-dotnet-v3/pull/5013" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/Azure/azure-cosmos-dotnet-v3/pull/5013/hovercard"&gt;5013&lt;/a&gt; Resiliency: Fixes a bug in the feature for "Faster detection of broken Transport connections".&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Set Environment variable AZURE_COSMOS_AGGRESSIVE_TIMEOUT_DETECTION_ENABLED to "True" to enable the above feature.  Fixed an issue where connections weren't marked as "unhealthy" under sustained failures, delaying recovery. Now, unhealthy connections trigger prompt reconnection, ensuring continuous client operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
                            &lt;/div&gt;
